children.subject: Is there a course website I can take a look at?

history.content:
<md>Hey everyone! If you’re looking for a 2 unit class at the intersection of data science and economics, check out Data 88E.

Data 88E: Economics Models examines economics concepts using data science methods and techniques with real-world datasets. Through the use of Python and Jupyter, the class re-examines fundamental economic concepts and surveys economics subdomains such as financial economics, macroeconomic policy, and econometrics. The class will also feature guest lecturers from industry and academia who will show how they apply concepts discussed in this class to their jobs and research. Previous guest lecturers have included speakers from Goldman Sachs and Harvard University.

This course also fulfills the lower division requirement for Data Science major’s Economics domain emphasis!
https://classes.berkeley.edu/content/2021-spring-data-88e-001-lec-001</md>
